items.title: Firefighters Battle Large Blaze at Bronx Apartment Building
items.description: Over 200 firefighters and emergency medical workers responded to the fire early Friday. Seven people have been injured and many residents displaced.

items.title: U.S. Imposes New Sanctions to Squeeze Russia’s Energy Sector
items.description: The Biden administration is cracking down on the Russian “shadow fleet” and taking steps to curb oil and gas production.

items.title: Rare Winter Storm Sweeps Across the South, Dumping Ice and Snow
items.description: The storm was sweeping across a wide swath of the South on Friday, dumping a mix of wintry precipitation from Oklahoma to Georgia.
